"title": "5744: wife",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5744",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The female partner in a marriage relationship. The origin of this God-ordained institution is traced back in the Bible to the Garden of Eden. Scripture stresses that marriage is a God-ordained institution, within which the husband should love and care for his wife, just as the wife should obey, honour and care for her husband. A good wife is portrayed as a great blessing, but a bad wife influences her husband for evil. In the OT, Israel is sometimes portrayed as God's wife; in the NT, the church is described as Christ's bride.</p>\n<h2>God's pattern for marriage</h2>\n<h3>Husband and wife are one flesh</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:23-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:23–2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:15\">MAL 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:4-Matt19:6\">MAT 19:4–19:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:6-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:6–10:9</a></p>\n<h3>The wife as helper and companion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:18\">GEN 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:20-Gen2:22\">GEN 2:20–2:22</a></p>\n<h3>The husband is head of the wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3\">1CO 11:3</a></p>\n<h3>The wife is the weaker partner</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16\">GEN 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>The Israelites were forbidden to take foreign wives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:3-Deut7:4\">DEU 7:3–7:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:16\">EXO 34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:12-Josh23:13\">JOS 23:12–23:13</a></p>\n<h2>Duties of a wife</h2>\n<h3>To submit to and respect her husband</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18\">COL 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph5:24\">EPH 5:22–5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:33\">EPH 5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:1–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>To care for her husband and household</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:10-Prov31:31\">PRO 31:10–31:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:4-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:4–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>To be faithful to her husband</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:14\">EXO 20:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:18\">DEU 5:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:11-Num5:31\">NUM 5:11–5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:27\">PRO 23:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:3-Matt14:4\">MAT 14:3–14:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:17-Mark6:18\">MRK 6:17–6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:12\">MRK 10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:19\">LUK 3:19</a></p>\n<h2>Advice on widows remarrying</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:39-1Cor7:40\">1CO 7:39–7:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:8-1Cor7:9\">1CO 7:8–7:9</a></p>\n<h2>Childless wives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21\">GEN 25:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:9-Gen18:15\">GEN 18:9–18:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:5\">JDG 13:2–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:9-1Sam1:20\">1SA 1:9–1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:5-Luke1:25\">LUK 1:5–1:25</a></p>\n<h2>Good wives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:10-Prov31:31\">PRO 31:10–31:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:11-1Sam19:17\">1SA 19:11–19:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:14-1Sam25:35\">1SA 25:14–25:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:4\">PRO 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:22\">PRO 18:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:14\">PRO 19:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:3-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:3–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:1–3:6</a></p>\n<h2>Wives giving good counsel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:19\">MAT 27:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:22-Judg13:23\">JDG 13:22–13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:10-Dan5:12\">DAN 5:10–5:12</a></p>\n<h2>Bad wives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:4\">PRO 12:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:13\">PRO 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:19\">PRO 21:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:24\">PRO 25:24</a></p>\n<h2>Wives influencing their husbands for evil</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8-Gen3:12\">GEN 3:8–3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:3-1Kgs11:4\">1KI 11:3–11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:20-1Kgs21:26\">1KI 21:20–21:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:9-Esth5:14\">EST 5:9–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:9\">JOB 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Israel as the wife of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:20\">JER 3:20</a></strong> <em>Israel's relationship with God was at times comparable to that of an unfaithful wife</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:5\">ISA 62:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:2\">JER 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:32\">EZK 16:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:2\">HOS 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:2\">HOS 2:2</a></p>\n<h2>The church as the bride of Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7\">REV 19:7</a></p>",
